The bot logs an IRC channel. This log can be used to stalk the members :) The bot is able to send the log via email to a given adress, and the logging mechanism is generic by using plugins.

An additional plugin is already implemented writing the log to a simple textfile. Just call the programm with the parameter "--plugin txt"

usage: ircbot.py [-h] [--server HOST] [--port PORT] [--nick NICK]
                   [--ident IDENT] [--real RNAME] [--channel CHANNEL] [-D]
                   [--mhost MHOST] [--maddress MADDRESS]
                   [--musername MUSERNAME] [--mpass MPASSWORD]
                   [--msubject MAIL_SUBJECT] [--plugin PLUGIN]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --server HOST         the IRC server
  --port PORT           the IRC port
  --nick NICK           the IRC nick
  --ident IDENT         the IRC ident
  --real RNAME          your IRC real name
  --channel CHANNEL     the IRC channel
  -D                    Deactivate deamon
  --mhost MHOST         your eMail host
  --maddress MADDRESS   your eMail address
  --musername MUSERNAME
                        your eMail username
  --mpass MPASSWORD     your eMail password
  --msubject MAIL_SUBJECT
                        the eMail subject
  --plugin PLUGIN       logging plugin